OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1780311775
OL,3,CWes Streeting backs North Sea oil
OL,4,Clicences and national insurance cut
OL,6,FLabour should consider cutting
OL,7,Fnational insurance and issuing new oil
OL,8,Fdrilling licences for the North Sea,
OL,9,FWes Streeting said as he continued to
OL,10,Fmake his pitch for the party's
OL,11,Fleadership.
OL,13,FIn a wide-ranging interview with the
OL,14,FSunday Times, the former health
OL,15,Fsecretary set out a series of policies
OL,16,Fahead of a potential leadership
OL,17,Fcontest expected by many in
OL,18,FWestminster within the coming months.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1780311775
OL,3,CWes Streeting backs North Sea oil
OL,4,Clicences and national insurance cut
OL,6,FHe reiterated his support for the UK's
OL,7,Feventual return to the EU, while
OL,8,Fsaying the party should stick to its
OL,9,Fmanifesto commitments on Europe in the
OL,10,Fshort term.
OL,12,FAnd he backed his possible opponent
OL,13,FAndy Burnham's support for more
OL,14,Fdevolution and greater state
OL,15,Fintervention in the market as "a good
OL,16,Fpro-fairness thing to do".
OL,26,@wD@_OUxD@YO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1780311775
OL,3,CWes Streeting backs North Sea oil
OL,4,Clicences and national insurance cut
OL,6,FBut Mr Streeting went further, arguing
OL,7,FLabour should issue more North Sea oil
OL,8,Fand gas licences, not because it would
OL,9,Freduce bills but because it would
OL,10,Fprovide additional tax revenue.
OL,12,FHe said: "We do have to take climate
OL,13,Fchange globally much more seriously
OL,14,Fand go aggressively towards more
OL,15,Frenewable energy.
OL,17,F"But there's sometimes a danger of
OL,18,FBritain wanting to lead the world. We
OL,19,Fcut off our own nose to spite our face
OL,20,Fwithout contributing to the greater
OL,21,Fwhole."
OL,26,@tD@JOUyD@AOU}D@GO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1780311775
OL,3,CWes Streeting backs North Sea oil
OL,4,Clicences and national insurance cut
OL,6,FHe also suggested he would be open to
OL,7,Freversing the increase in employers'
OL,8,Fnational insurance contributions
OL,9,Fintroduced by Rachel Reeves in her
OL,10,Ffirst budget in order to boost
OL,11,Femployment, particularly among young
OL,12,Fpeople.
OL,14,FMr Streeting said: "I think we should
OL,15,Fbe thinking actively about how to
OL,16,Fincentivise, whether that's through
OL,17,Ftargeted reduction in employers'
OL,18,Fnational insurance or other kinds of
OL,19,Frecruitment and retention incentives."
OL,26,@vD@TOU{D@fO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1780311775
OL,3,CWes Streeting backs North Sea oil
OL,4,Clicences and national insurance cut
OL,6,FThese positions echoed those taken by
OL,7,Fformer prime minister Sir Tony Blair
OL,8,Fin an essay criticising some of
OL,9,FLabour's policies and accusing the
OL,10,FGovernment of lacking a "coherent
OL,11,Fplan".
OL,13,FMr Streeting told the Times that
OL,14,FLabour had come to power
OL,15,F"underprepared" and "lacking any sort
OL,16,Fof intellectual curiosity".
OL,26,@rD@YOUsD@EO]wD@AOUwD@OO]wD@UOUxD@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1780311775
OL,3,CWes Streeting backs North Sea oil
OL,4,Clicences and national insurance cut
OL,6,FBut he also said he would give Sir
OL,7,FTony "a flea in his ear" over some of
OL,8,Fhis suggestions, particularly on
OL,9,Fartificial intelligence ` suggesting
OL,10,Fthe former prime minister had made
OL,11,Farguments he would not have done in
OL,12,Foffice.
OL,14,FHe said: "Blair's done himself a
OL,15,Fdisservice proposing a prescription
OL,16,Fthat was absent of any values.
OL,26,@oD@FOUoD@XO]vD@JOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1780311775
OL,3,CWes Streeting backs North Sea oil
OL,4,Clicences and national insurance cut
OL,6,F"I feel the Tony Blair of 1997, or the
OL,7,FTony Blair of 2007 for that matter,
OL,8,Fwould have been making an argument
OL,9,Fthat said, okay, big revolution
OL,10,Fcoming, how do we apply traditional
OL,11,Fvalues in a modern setting?"
OL,13,FMeanwhile, Sir Tony himself defended
OL,14,Fhis essay against criticism from
OL,15,Ffigures within Labour such as Mr
OL,16,FBurnham who argued he had paid too
OL,17,Flittle attention to inequality.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
